com.bertramlabs.plugins.karman
[Groovy] Class Directory

java.lang.Object
  com.bertramlabs.plugins.karman.Directory
All Implemented Interfaces:
DirectoryInterface
abstract class Directory

This is an abstract class implementation for managing directories / buckets in the cloud.

Typically you would not use this class directly but rather use an implementation of this class. (i.e. LocalDirectory)

Example Usage: 

 Directory dir = new Directory(provider: provider, name: name)

 if(!dir.exists()) {
     dir.mkdir()    
 }
 //List all files recursively
 dir.listFiles()

 //List Files in a sub"folder"
 dir.listFiles(prefix: 'config/')
Authors:
David Estes
